cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper is about monocular depth estimation using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel network architecture, which involves the use of local planar guidance layers, indicating that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The paper also evaluates its proposed method on challenging benchmarks, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for depth estimation, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.GR (Graphics).
